{
  "info": {
    "name": "IncidentPilot — Monitoring Stack APIs",
    "description": "Complete Postman collection for the IncidentPilot monitoring stack.\n\nBase URLs:\n  FastAPI Generator — http://localhost:5001\n  Prometheus        — http://localhost:9090\n  Loki              — http://localhost:3100\n  Grafana           — http://localhost:3000 (admin / admin)\n  Gradio UI         — http://localhost:7860 (browser only, no REST API)\n\nUsage workflow:\n  1. Start the stack: docker compose up -d\n  2. Verify health with FastAPI /health -> Prometheus /-/ready -> Loki /ready -> Grafana /api/health\n  3. Trigger an incident: POST /api/incidents/pool/trigger\n  4. Watch metrics change: GET /api/incidents/state (every 3s)\n  5. Query Prometheus for the latest metric values\n  6. Query Loki for application logs\n  7. Open Grafana dashboards (http://localhost:3000, admin/admin, \"Incidents\" folder)\n\nFastAPI auto-generates OpenAPI documentation:\n  - Swagger UI: http://localhost:5001/docs\n  - ReDoc:      http://localhost:5001/redoc\n  - OpenAPI:    http://localhost:5001/openapi.json",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "IncidentPilot"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "api_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:5001",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "prometheus_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:9090",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "loki_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:3100",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "grafana_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:3000",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "🟢 1. Health Checks",
      "description": "Verify all 4 Docker services are running and responsive.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "FastAPI Generator — /health",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{api_url}}/health"
            },
            "description": "Returns the FastAPI generator's operational status and whether an incident is currently active."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status 200\", () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test(\"Body has service field\", () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('service', 'incident-generator');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('status', 'ok');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('request_id');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.request_id).to.match(/^[a-f0-9]{12}$/);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has X-Request-ID header\", () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('X-Request-ID')).to.match(/^[a-f0-9]{12}$/);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "No active incident",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [
                {
                  "key": "Content-Type",
                  "value": "application/json"
                },
                {
                  "key": "X-Request-ID",
                  "value": "a1b2c3d4e5f6"
                }
              ],
              "body": "{\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"service\": \"incident-generator\",\n  \"active_incidents\": [],\n  \"request_id\": \"a1b2c3d4e5f6\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "Pool incident active",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [],
              "body": "{\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"service\": \"incident-generator\",\n  \"active_incidents\": [\"pool@checkout-api\"],\n  \"request_id\": \"a1b2c3d4e5f6\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Prometheus — /-/ready",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{prometheus_url}}/-/ready"
            },
            "description": "Prometheus readiness endpoint. Returns 200 when Prometheus is ready to accept queries."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status 200\", () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test(\"Body contains 'Prometheus Ready'\", () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.text()).to.include('Prometheus');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Prometheus Ready",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [],
              "body": "Prometheus is Ready.\n"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Loki — /ready",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{loki_url}}/ready"
            },
            "description": "Loki readiness endpoint. Returns 200 when Loki is ready to accept logs and queries."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status 200\", () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Loki Ready",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [],
              "body": "Ready\n"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Grafana — /api/health",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Basic YWRtaW46YWRtaW4=",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{grafana_url}}/api/health"
            },
            "description": "Grafana health check. Requires Basic Auth (admin / admin)."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status 200\", () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test(\"Body has database field\", () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('database', 'ok');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Grafana Healthy",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [],
              "body": "{\n  \"database\": \"ok\",\n  \"version\": \"11.2.0\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "⚡ 2. Incident Simulator (FastAPI)",
      "description": "Trigger, monitor, and resolve simulated production incidents via the FastAPI generator.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Trigger — Pool Exhaustion",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{api_url}}/api/incidents/pool/trigger"
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"auto_resolve\": true\n}"
            },
            "description": "Start a Postgres connection-pool exhaustion scenario.\n\nLifecycle: climbing (15s) → plateau (15s) → recovering (10s) → auto-resolve"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status 200\", () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test(\"Scenario started\", () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('status', 'started');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('kind', 'pool');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('phase');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('request_id');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.request_id).to.match(/^[a-f0-9]{12}$/);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has X-Request-ID header\", () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('X-Request-ID')).to.match(/^[a-f0-9]{12}$/);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Pool started",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [
                {
                  "key": "X-Request-ID",
                  "value": "a1b2c3d4e5f6"
                }
              ],
              "body": "{\n  \"status\": \"started\",\n  \"kind\": \"pool\",\n  \"phase\": \"climbing\",\n  \"tick_count\": 0,\n  \"request_id\": \"a1b2c3d4e5f6\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Trigger — Cache Failover",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
